PFD: 06-Jan-26
HB116 Enrolled
1 Enrolled, An Act,
2
3
4 Relating to emergency medical services personnel education; to
5 amend Sections 22-18-60, 22-18-61, 22-18-62, and 22-18-64,
6 Code of Alabama 1975, to further provide for the Volunteer
7 Rescue Squad Tuition Reimbursement Program by authorizing the
8 Alabama Department of Public Health, through its designated
9 regional agencies of the Office of Emergency Medical Services,
10 to provide education and receive tuition reimbursement under
11 the program; and to make nonsubstantive, technical revisions
12 to update the existing code language to current style.
13 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF ALABAMA:
14 Section 1. Sections 22-18-60, 22-18-61, 22-18-62, and
15 22-18-64, Code of Alabama 1975, are amended to read as
16 follows:
17 "§22-18-60
18 For the purposes of this article, the following terms
19 shall have the following meanings:
20 (1) ACCS. The Alabama Community College System.
21 (2) AMBULANCE SERVICE. An ambulance service located in
22 this state which is a member of the Alabama Association of
23 Ambulance Services.
24 (3) ASSOCIATIONS. The Alabama Association of Rescue
25 Squads, the Alabama Association of Volunteer Fire Departments,
26 or the Alabama Association of Ambulance Services.
27 (4) DESIGNATED EMS REGIONAL AGENCY. A regional agency
28 of the Office of Emergency Medical Services of the Alabama
