of the Office of Emergency Medical Services of the Alabama
HB116 Enrolled
29 Department of Public Health which is designated by the
30 department to offer educational courses to students.
31 (5) ELIGIBLE EDUCATIONAL INSTITUTION. A member school
32 of the ACCS, the fire college, the University of South
33 Alabama, or a designated regional EMS agency.
34 (4)(6) EMERGENCY MEDICAL SERVICE PERSONNEL (EMSP). All
35 recognized levels of personnel licensed by the Alabama
36 Department of Public Health, who have met all primary or
37 renewal educational requirements, or both, set by the Alabama
38 Department of Public Health, and who are allowed to provide
39 medical care within the level of their scope of practice
40 granted by the Office of Emergency Medical Services within the
41 Alabama Department of Public Health.
42 (5)(7) FIRE COLLEGE. The Alabama Fire College.
43 (6)(8) STUDENT. A student enrolled in an emergency
44 medical services certification program at a member institution
45 of the ACCS, the fire college, or the University of South
46 Alabamaan eligible educational institution.
47 (7)(9) TUITION COSTS. Includes the actual cost of
48 tuition and fees required to complete an approved
49 courseprogram of instruction for EMSP certification, as
50 determined by each eligible educational institution.
51 (8)(11) VOLUNTEER RESCUE SQUAD. A volunteer rescue
52 squad located in this state andthat is a member of the Alabama
53 Association of Rescue Squads.
54 (9)(10) VOLUNTEER FIRE DEPARTMENT. A volunteer fire
55 department located in this state."
56 "§22-18-61
Page 2

"§22-18-61
HB116 Enrolled
57 (a) The ACCS, the fire college, and the University of
58 South AlabamaEligible educational institutions, in
59 consultation with the associations, shall jointly develop and
60 administer a student tuition reimbursement program for
61 students who contract to provide two years of emergency
62 medical services for volunteer rescue squads, volunteer fire
63 departments, or ambulance services after becoming a licensed
64 EMSP.
65 (b)(1) Tuition reimbursement under this article shall
66 cover tuition costs paid by the student or the volunteer
67 rescue squad, volunteer fire department, ambulance service, or
68 association on behalf of the student of which the student is a
69 member. Tuition paid by the volunteer rescue squad, volunteer
70 fire department, ambulance service, or association shall be
71 reimbursed directly to the volunteer rescue squad, volunteer
72 fire department, ambulance service, or association.
73 (2) Tuition reimbursement under this article shall not
74 include any tuition costs covered by grants or other monetary
75 awards provided to a student including, but not limited to,
76 federal education grants and scholarships, as determined by
77 the ACCS.
78 (3) Tuition costs shall not be reimbursed until the
79 student provides ACCS and the associations with documentation
80 that he or she has successfully completed the approved
81 courseprogram of instruction, proof of passing the
82 certification exam, production of a valid EMSP license from
83 the Alabama Department of Public Health, and a contractual
84 agreement to comply with the service requirements.
Page 3

agreement to comply with the service requirements.
HB116 Enrolled
85 (c) In the event that a tuition reimbursement recipient
86 fails to meet the service requirements for any reason other
87 than extreme hardship as defined within the joint agreement
88 required in Section 22-18-64(b), the individual shall be
89 deemed to have breached the underlying contract and shall be
90 liable in the form of monetary damages to the state for the
91 immediate repayment of the total tuition costs reimbursed,
92 plus interest at the rate of eight percent. The associations
93 shall notify ACCS of recipients who fail to meet the service
94 requirements.
95 (d) Beginning with the 2023-2024 fiscal year, the
96 amount of tuition reimbursement available to students shall be
97 divided among volunteer fire departments, rescue squads, and
98 ambulance services based on available appropriations. in
99 compliance with the following standards:
100 (1) The ACCS shall create operational procedures to
101 ensure that funds and volunteer service commitments are split
102 equitably among volunteer fire departments, rescue squads, and
103 ambulance services. Notwithstanding the foregoing, priority
104 shall be given to volunteer fire departments, rescue squads,
105 and nonprofit ambulance services.
106 (2) The Alabama Department of Public Health shall adopt
107 a rule imposing a monetary cap on the amount of tuition costs
108 that may be reimbursed for students who complete the program
109 of instruction through a designated regional EMS agency, which
110 shall not exceed any cap in effect on the amount of reimbursed
111 tuition costs for the Alabama Fire College."
112 "§22-18-62
