"§22-18-62
HB116 Enrolled
113 Beginning October 1, 2018, the member(a) Member
114 institutions of the ACCS, the Fire Collegefire college, and
115 the University of South Alabama, and designated EMS regional
116 agencies may enter into contracts with new students seeking to
117 obtain certification as an EMSP.
118 (b) The Alabama Department of Public Health shall adopt
119 rules setting credentialing and accreditation standards for
120 private companies and instructors that teach courses on behalf
121 of the designated EMS regional agencies which are equal to the
122 standards of the other eligible education institutions."
123 "§22-18-64
124 (a) The ACCS shall annually report on the condition and
125 accomplishments of the tuition reimbursement program to the
126 Governor, Speaker of the House of Representatives, President
127 Pro Tempore of the Senate, the Chair of the House Ways and
128 Means Education Committee, the Chair of the Senate Finance and
129 Taxation Education Committee, and the Deputy Director of the
130 Legislative Services Agency, Fiscal Division. The report shall
131 include the number of students participating in the program
132 and the amount of tuition reimbursed for the reporting year.
133 The memberEligible educational institutions of the ACCS, the
134 fire college, and the University of South Alabama shall
135 provide this information to ACCS for inclusion in the annual
136 report. The report shall be submitted by the fifth legislative
137 day of each regular session of the Legislature.
138 (b) The ACCS, the fire college, and the University of
139 South Alabama shall enter into a joint agreement with the
140 other eligible educational institutions to implement and
Page 5

other eligible educational institutions to implement and
HB116 Enrolled
141 administer the tuition reimbursement program, which shall
142 include provisions for ensuring that operational expenses for
143 the program in a fiscal year do not exceed 10 percent of the
144 funding for the program in that fiscal year. The joint
145 agreement shall provide for limiting the acceptance of
146 applications for the program or limiting tuition
147 reimbursements when necessary, or both.
148 (c) Any monies received for the operations of the
149 tuition reimbursement program, including repayments, interest,
150 and penalties paid because of failure to honor service
151 requirements, shall be used to fund tuition reimbursements."
152 Section 2. This act shall become effective on October
153 1, 2026.
